OL,6,FLiam West, 31, of Rochford, Essex, who
OL,7,Fskippered a tug that towed the barge
OL,8,Fwas jailed for 14 years and
OL,9,Faccomplices Christopher Mealey, 47, of
OL,10,FLiverpool, and Paul Farrell, 44, of
OL,11,FBolton, were jailed for 22 years and
OL,12,F23 years respectively.
OL,14,FNCA operations manager Jules Harriman
OL,15,Fsaid: "This OCG clearly had
OL,16,Finternational connections and was able
OL,17,Fto orchestrate crimes with accomplices
OL,18,Fabroad that damaged the UK.
